A LITTLE TREE

WITH A BIG HISTORY

Bonsai began in China as "penjing" over 1,000 years ago. It spread to Japan, evolving into an art of shaping miniature trees with Zen philosophy.

Samurai and monks refined it, symbolizing balance and patience. By the 20th century, bonsai gained global recognition, blending nature, tradition, and artistry.
